cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of 3D human pose estimation from images using convolutional neural networks. The use of end-to-end learning and the incorporation of 2D pose information also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on joint positions and relative positions also suggests that it could belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of image features and the evaluation on a dataset suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
